            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 6,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1371151171,
            "creation_date": 1371151171,
            "body": "<p>The order of an algorithm does not tell you how quickly it runs. It tells you how its speed evolves when the size of n changes.<\/p>\n\n<p>Being O(n) = n^2 means that if you try this with 10,000,000 elements, you will need (approx) 4 times the current time needed.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 17095290,
            "question_id": 17095258
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/978a9f5060338657ddeb3781c6a3a2c8?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 350538,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 688653,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/688653/zw324",
                "reputation": 27205,
                "display_name": "zw324",
                "accept_rate": 100
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1371151464,
            "creation_date": 1371151163,
            "body": "<p>Could be that JIT kicks in and optimized things away, since the double loop does not actually do anything.<\/p>\n\n<p>Note this is too specific for each version and implementation of Java and JVM - on my version it's running for about a minute now.<\/p>\n\n<p>You might add a<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>System.out.println(x)\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>after and outside the for loops just to stop the optimization, if you want to see O(N^2) behavior. <\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 17095286,
            "question_id": 17095258,
            "last_edit_date": 1371151464
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/7ecc13b224d79ba7854d6e83c028761f?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
                "account_id": 1637497,
                "user_type": "registered",
